{{Infobox religious building |building_name = Ang Chee Sia Ong |image = Ang Chee Sia Ong Temple main hall.JPG |image_size = 350px |caption = Ang Chee Sia Ong Temple main hall |map_type = |map_size = |map_caption = |location = |geo = {{coord|1|18|41.28|N|103|45|37.66|E}} |latitude = |longitude = |religious_affiliation =[[Taoism]], [[Mahayana Buddhism]] and [[Confucianism]] |rite = |region = |state = |province = |territory = |prefecture = [[Singapore]] |sector = |district = |cercle = |municipality = [[Singapore]] |consecration_year = 1997 |status = |functional_status = |heritage_designation = |leadership = |website = |architecture = |architect = |architecture_type = |architecture_style = |general_contractor = |facade_direction = |groundbreaking = |year_completed = 1997 |construction_cost = |specifications = |capacity = |length = |width = |width_nave = |height_max = |dome_quantity = |dome_height_outer = |dome_height_inner = |dome_dia_outer = |dome_dia_inner = |minaret_quantity = |minaret_height = |spire_quantity = |spire_height = |materials = |nrhp = |added = |refnum = |designated = }}
'''Ang Chee Sia Ong Temple''' ({{zh|s=安济圣王庙}}) is a [[Taoist]], [[Mahayana Buddhism]] and [[Confucianism]] temple located in [[West Coast, Singapore|West Coast]], [[Singapore]]. The main hall is dedicated to the Chinese goddess Mazu, the left top is dedicated to Confucius and the Bodhisattva Guan yin.
There are also various other deities enshrined in the temple, including the [[Doumu]].
