==Connection to Essenes==

As Talmudic sources never mention the [[Essenes]] but do mention the Boethusians, while Greek sources (including Josephus) never mention the Boethusians as such but mention the Essenes as a prominent group, and as the Essenes are often identified with the sect that produced the [[Dead Sea Scrolls]], which do indeed bear some similarity to views attributed to the Boethusians by the Talmud, the suggestion has been made<ref>https://books.google.co.il/books?id=KZC_tBzZs1EC&pg=PA105&lpg=PA105&dq=boethusians+essenes&source=bl&ots=fGonLay8tP&sig=KDukLZ1pREJLTgQmfA6cvDkr5Xc&hl=iw&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwiEoKHgrOHLAhWEXCwKHVetDm4Q6AEIIjAB#v=onepage&q=boethusians%20essenes&f=false</ref> that the two groups were more or less identical, the word "Boethusian" being a corruption of "Beit Essaya," or "House of Essenes."<ref>http://www.britannica.com/topic/Boethusian</ref> This is admittedly a highly speculative position with little actual evidence to back it up, but is sometimes seen as the most likely explanation at the very least.

