The word "'''''prayojana'''''" is a [[Sanskrit]] [[Terminology|term]] which denotes the ultimate goal or object of attainment. Along with [[sambandha]] and [[abhidheya]], prayojana is one of the three fundamental concepts in [[Gaudiya Vaishnava]] [[theology]], where it is used to describe the ultimate goal of life - [[Prem (Hinduism)|Prem]]a, or pure love of [[Krishna]].
