[[File:Siddha Shila.svg|thumb|Siddhashila as per the [[Jain cosmology]]]]
{{Jainism}}
'''Siddhashila''' is an area in [[Jain cosmology]] at the apex of the universe, which is where the [[Jainism|Jains]] believe people who have become ''[[Arihant (Jainism)|arihant]]s'', or people with infinite knowledge, go after they die and attain ''[[Moksha (Jainism)|moksha]]''. Such people are called ''[[Siddha#Jainism|siddhas]]'' after they discard their mortal body, hence the origin of the term.<ref>{{cite book |title=The Culture of India |last=Kuiper |first=Kathleen |page=150 |year=2010 |publisher=[[Rosen Publishing Group]] |isbn=9781615301492}}</ref>

