In [[Australian Aboriginal mythology]], '''Tjinimin''' is the ancestor of the [[Australian Aborigine|Australian people]]s.  He is associated with the [[bat]] and with Kunmanggur the [[rainbow serpent]].

One story of Tjinimin tells of an argument between him and the Great [[Rainbow Serpent]] where Tjinimin wanted to have sex with Great Rainbow Serpent's consorts, the Green Parrot-Girls.  Upon losing Tjinimin hung upside down in a tree and admired the stars, vowing to never have sex again.  Soon after, his nose falls off, supposedly explaining to the native culture why [[bat]]s in the region have such short noses.

